

This project can be further developed into a complete intelligent fault detection and monitoring system for electronic and embedded devices. Currently, the system detects basic logic and output faults using machine learning techniques. In future versions, the project will be enhanced with a graphical user interface (GUI) using Python Tkinter to provide a more interactive and user-friendly application experience.

The project can also be integrated with hardware platforms such as Arduino, Raspberry Pi, sensors, and FPGA boards for real-time fault monitoring and analysis. Sensor data collected from hardware devices can be processed by the AI model to predict whether the system is operating normally or developing faults. If any abnormal behavior is detected, the system can automatically generate warnings or alerts.

Future improvements may include detection of:

* Real hardware failures
* Overheating issues
* Voltage instability
* Sensor malfunctions
* IC/component faults

The project also has potential applications in embedded systems, VLSI testing, industrial automation, IoT devices, and predictive maintenance systems. With further development, advanced machine learning models and real-time monitoring dashboards can be integrated to improve accuracy, visualization, and automation capabilities.
